# Project Structure and Entry Points

Use this rule to quickly locate where to implement features or fixes.

- Main window and runner: [src/traffic_sim/render/app.py](mdc:src/traffic_sim/render/app.py)
- Module entrypoint: [src/traffic_sim/__main__.py](mdc:src/traffic_sim/__main__.py)
- Simulation core:
  - Track geometry/safety: [src/traffic_sim/core/track.py](mdc:src/traffic_sim/core/track.py)
  - Simulation setup/loop: [src/traffic_sim/core/simulation.py](mdc:src/traffic_sim/core/simulation.py)
  - Vehicles/state: [src/traffic_sim/core/vehicle.py](mdc:src/traffic_sim/core/vehicle.py)
  - Drivers/params (scaffold): [src/traffic_sim/core/driver.py](mdc:src/traffic_sim/core/driver.py)
  - HUD helpers: [src/traffic_sim/core/hud.py](mdc:src/traffic_sim/core/hud.py)
  - Event logging: [src/traffic_sim/core/logging.py](mdc:src/traffic_sim/core/logging.py)
- Configuration:
  - Loader/helpers: [src/traffic_sim/config/loader.py](mdc:src/traffic_sim/config/loader.py)
  - Default config: [config/config.yaml](mdc:config/config.yaml)
- Data catalogs:
  - Vehicles: [src/traffic_sim/models/vehicle_specs.py](mdc:src/traffic_sim/models/vehicle_specs.py)
  - Drivers (distributions): [src/traffic_sim/models/driver_specs.py](mdc:src/traffic_sim/models/driver_specs.py)
- Specification: [docs/spec.md](mdc:docs/spec.md)
- Tasks and tooling:
  - Task runner: [Taskfile.yml](mdc:Taskfile.yml)
  - Project metadata/deps: [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml)
  - Pre-commit: [.pre-commit-config.yaml](mdc:.pre-commit-config.yaml)
  - CI workflow: [.github/workflows/ci.yml](mdc:.github/workflows/ci.yml)

Notes:
- The stadium track is parameterized by total length and straight fraction; do not hard-code pixel sizes in core logic.
- The safety panel is computed in the core and rendered in the window; geometry is not constrained by safety.

